    The `alias` command is used to add and remove aliases.

    ## Usage

    ```sh
    zulu alias <context> [args]
    ```

    ### `zulu alias`

    List all of the aliases currently defined in `~/.config/zulu/alias.

    ### `zulu alias add <alias> <command>`

    Adds an alias to the environment, and registers it to be loaded in the next shell session.

    ```sh
    zulu alias add l 'ls -la'
    ``` 

    ### `zulu alias rm <alias>`

    Remove an alias.

    ```sh
    zulu alias rm l
    ```

    ### `zulu alias add -g <alias>`

    Add a global alias

    ```sh
    zulu alias add -g G ' | grep'
    ```

    ### `zulu alias load`

    Loads all aliases in `~/.config/zulu/alias` into the environment.
